snippet.textDisplay: Lisa Gibbons said that 2020 is the start of a new decade.  Sorry Lisa, 2020 is the end of the current decade.  Year 1 is the start of the first decade.  Year 11 is the start of the second decade.  2000 years later, 2011 is the start of the current decade.  Therefore, 2021 is the start of the next new decade.  Share this simple math with your friends who might mistakenly think that 2020 is the start of a new decade.

snippet.textDisplay: Thank you so much, KTLA, for the coverage of the parade. I was so glad to find your live stream on FB earlier today. It was so great to be able view the beautiful floats and hear all of the bands without cutting away to a commercial about an upcoming program. I was particularly glad to see the band from West Harrison in Mississippi. I live in Mississippi and have followed the development of that band program. It's hard to believe that school was opened only 10 years ago. They had a very good band program from day 1 but have certainly made great strides each year and have become one of the top marching bands in their classification at state marching competition for the last several years. Thanks again for a job well-done.
snippet.textOriginal: Thank you so much, KTLA, for the coverage of the parade. I was so glad to find your live stream on FB earlier today. It was so great to be able view the beautiful floats and hear all of the bands without cutting away to a commercial about an upcoming program. snippet.textDisplay: As someone who marched in many parades as a teenager, no, no, no to any equestrian units ahead of any marching unit.  Horses are not house trained, and they leave large mementos of their passing.  In my area, at least for the last two years I was active, we managed to convince most of the sponsors of parades in our area to group the horses with the last few floats.  In this parade, I would keep them with floats which try to drown out the bands with their music.
